JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s official opposition party the Democratic Alliance said on Friday it would ask parliament to launch a &#8220;full-scale&#8221; investigation into state power utility Eskom&#8217;s decision to reappoint Brian Molefe as its chief executive.Read: Brian Molefe returns to Eskom (without the R30m)Eskom said earlier on Friday that Molefe would return as its chief executive on Monday after the board revoked its decision to grant him early retirement. 